<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-061  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 061.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Business  Oct 29 1990 v16 n20 p59(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Export improvements loom on the Eastern front. (includes a relatedarticle on export regulations)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chase, Martyn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Opportunities are opening for the US technology exports due to thepolitical turmoil in Eastern Europe.andP;  The electronics industrywants the Coordinating Committee for Multilateral Export Controls(COCOM) and the US Congress to lift further restrictions onhigh-tech exports and to develop a new export control system whichtakes into account the new realities of the post-Cold War era.andO;COCOM has agreed to decontrol 30 of the 120 categories of thecontrolled products, but the industry is asking for more.andP;  Beforelifting more controls, safeguards must be put into place, such asa political statement to prevent the diversion of technology, apaperwork system to track where goods are going, and a legalframework to control exports.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic IndustryExportGovernment RegulationEastern EuropeHigh TechnologyCoordinating Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsInternational TradePolitical Issues.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>